## 5. What Problems Software Services Solves

Software Services should be understood through the problems it solves.

Common problems may include:

### 5.1 Production tools that are implemented but not fully aligned with the real workflow
Organizations may have adopted software such as production tracking platforms, but the configuration may not reflect how teams actually hand off work, track assets, review progress, or coordinate between departments.

### 5.2 Too much manual work inside the pipeline
Teams may rely on repetitive actions, manual file handling, ad hoc naming processes, fragmented task updates, or disconnected review steps that slow down production and increase the chance of errors.

### 5.3 Disconnected tools and fragmented data
Studios and production teams often use multiple platforms across scheduling, production tracking, file sharing, game engine workflows, ticketing, rendering, review, and storage. When those tools do not communicate effectively, teams lose visibility and waste time moving information manually.

### 5.4 Workflow friction during live production
Creative teams cannot always pause work to redesign their systems. They need implementation and optimization work that can happen around active production without creating disruption.

### 5.5 Lack of documentation, training, or long-term workflow support
Even when systems are implemented, teams may lack usable documentation, internal adoption, support processes, or an ongoing improvement path as production grows.

### 5.6 Pipeline scaling challenges
What works for one team or one studio may break down as productions become more complex, more distributed, or more reliant on external partners and hybrid environments.

These themes are directly supported by the language on GPL's Software Services page, which emphasizes removing friction, streamlining file handling, reducing errors, integrating tools, supporting live productions, documenting systems, and helping teams scale cleanly from single studios to distributed teams. :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}

