## 9. Relationship to Other GPL Business Units

This section is important because it helps prevent overlap and confusion in future prompts.

### 9.1 Software Services vs Managed Services
Managed Services focuses on the stability, support, security, and performance of infrastructure and day-to-day IT operations.

Software Services focuses on the configuration, customization, integration, and workflow optimization of the software systems that teams use to run production and operations.

A useful distinction is:

- Managed Services keeps the environment running.
- Software Services helps the workflow inside that environment run better.

### 9.2 Software Services vs Consulting
Consulting is more strategic and advisory. It may help organizations decide what direction to take, what tools to evaluate, or how to think about scale, workflow maturity, or transformation.

Software Services is more execution-oriented. It helps implement, customize, connect, and support the systems that teams will actually use.

### 9.3 Software Services vs Security & Compliance
Security & Compliance focuses on risk reduction, protected workflows, regulatory or framework alignment, cybersecurity posture, and services such as TPN-related support.

Software Services can interact with secure environments, but its primary role is not compliance governance. Its role is to make workflow systems function effectively.

### 9.4 Software Services as a Bridge Layer
Software Services can often act as a bridge between GPL's infrastructure expertise and the day-to-day operational reality of the client. It is the layer where systems, workflows, and users meet.

This makes it especially valuable in organizations where the technical environment is already in place, but workflow friction remains high.

